In the yaml, we include all of the following in the header:

  • <script src="paged.polyfill.js"></script>
    This is the default source for Paged.js, which must be included in the header for any of this to work.
  • <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="print.css">
    Paged.js uses this to control what happens to the layout when you click âPrintâ in your browser.
  • <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="preview.css" media="screen">
    Gives the content a paged look when viewed in your browser. Note the media="screen" attribute! Itâs required!
